# Wade-O-Lution workspace

This workspace commonly includes **data-api** (backend), **integrity-ts** (frontend), **data-api-terraform-provider**, **core-cluster-charts**, **device-configuration**, and **data-api-sdk** (stub).

## Harness layout

| Scope | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Platform (all repos) | `~/.cursor/rules/`, `~/.cursor/skills/` |
| Backend | `data-api/.cursor/` |
| Frontend | `integrity-ts/.cursor/` |
| Terraform provider | `data-api-terraform-provider/AGENTS.md` + `.cursor/rules/` |
| Helm / ArgoCD | `core-cluster-charts/AGENTS.md` + `.cursor/rules/` |
| Device config API | `device-configuration/AGENTS.md` + `.cursor/rules/` |
| SDK (placeholder) | No harness until code exists |
| Meeting notes KB platform | `meeting_notes_workflow/.cursor/` (`00-orchestrator.mdc` + `project.mdc`) |
| Mac mini lab infra | `Integrity_Lab/.cursor/` (`agent-orchestrator.mdc` + `project.mdc`) |
| Swarm composition plane | `repo-index/.cursor/` (`swarm-protocol.mdc`) |

**Spec Kit ownership:** `meeting_notes_workflow/.cursor/skills/speckit-*` (and `overengineering-*`, `skill-supply-chain-review`, `notion-integration`) are **repo-canonical**. The matching `~/.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` copies are short pointer stubs with `disable-model-invocation: true` â€” they exist for non-repo chats/other machines, not as a second source of truth. Edit the meeting_notes copy; do not hand-edit the global stub body beyond the pointer + minimal fallback.

## Cross-repo work

- Contracts: `integrity-ts/.cursor/skills/cross-repo-contract-sync/SKILL.md` (canonical)
- Live cutover: `integrity-ts/.cursor/skills/contract-graduation/SKILL.md` (canonical)
- data-api stubs: `.cursor/skills/cross-repo-contract-sync/`, `contract-graduation/` (pointers only)
- Handoff: `~/.cursor/rules/compact-handoff.mdc` + `~/.cursor/skills/session-handoff/SKILL.md`

Edit the **integrity-ts canonical** skill when changing cross-repo procedure; data-api stubs must stay pointers only.

## Automatic skill routing

| Layer | Path |
|-------|------|
| Router script | `~/.cursor/hooks/workspace-skill-router.sh` |
| User hook | `~/.cursor/hooks.json` (schema **version 1**) â†’ `beforeSubmitPrompt` |
| Per-repo hook | `<repo>/.cursor/hooks.json` (version 1; sets `WADE_REPO_KEY` via wrapper script) |
| Mandate rule | `~/.cursor/rules/skill-routing-mandate.mdc` |

On each prompt, hooks emit **MANDATORY SKILL ROUTING** with absolute paths to skills/rules to read before edits. Extend keywords in `workspace-skill-router.sh` when adding skills.

**Cursor:** Enable **Hooks** in Cursor Settings if routing does not appear. Reload the window after harness changes.

Override workspace root: `export WADE_O_LUTION_WORKSPACE=/path/to/Wade-O-Lution-Inc`

Any recognized repo above (`ACTIVE_REPO` non-empty) also gets this rule
itself added once per prompt via `add_global_rule` in
`route_repo_context_boost` â€” a cheap, always-on cross-repo context boost, not
a global `alwaysApply`.

## Quality gates (by repo)

- **data-api:** `uv run pytest`, `basedpyright`, `ruff`
- **integrity-ts:** `npm run build`, `npm run test`

## MCP: intentionally empty

`~/.cursor/mcp.json` has `"mcpServers": {}` on purpose, not by omission. Live
MCP tool descriptors cost real context per session (e.g. Notion's plugin is
~28K tokens â€” see `notion-integration` skill), and most cross-service work in
this workspace goes through in-repo service layers or dedicated CLIs
(Doppler, Supabase, Grafana, Fireflies) instead. Enable a specific MCP
plugin/server only for the session that actually needs live calls; do not
leave servers registered globally "just in case."

## CLI permissions posture

`~/.cursor/cli-config.json`: `approvalMode: "allowlist"`, `sandbox.mode:
"disabled"`. Sandbox is off deliberately â€” agents in this workspace need
full local tooling (`doppler run`, `uv`, `supabase`, `terraform`, ssh to the
mac mini) that a sandbox would block or require constant re-approval for;
this is a conscious "trust the allowlist, not the sandbox" tradeoff, not an
oversight. The allowlist itself stays **minimal and read-only**: `Shell(ls)`,
`Shell(git status)`, `Shell(git diff)`, `Shell(git log)`. Do not add
installers, `git push --force`, `terraform apply`, or anything destructive to
the allowlist â€” those stay one approval click away on purpose.
